  <brief_title>A Pediatric Safety and Pharmacokinetics Study of Ha44 Gel Administered Topically for Treatment of Head Lice Infestation</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hatchtech Pty Ltd</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hatchtech Pty Ltd</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary purpose of the study is to evaluate safety and tolerability of a single
      application of Ha44 Gel 0.74% w/w for the treatment of head lice. Secondary purpose is to
      evaluate PK of Ha44 and benzyl alcohol under conditions of maximal exposure in pediatric
      population.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
